Ajj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"recUn6eVJDoG4xI0j","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAjj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"recLcxRZbz3yIQB7b","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAjj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"recEP3QZ3HUmIkv4Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAjj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"recVMgLyBVZ3c8jaf","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recAjj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"recCh323mcqdG01EW","label":"event"},{"source":"recAjj4tqd7L0gzqU","target":"receNV351SLbofU0a","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rechojCqifQwluNv5","ref":"2Kgs.3.1","text":"Now Jehoram the son of Ahab began to reign over Israel in Samaria the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned twelve years."},{"id":"recdDy9gWSRZe3duu","ref":"2Kgs.3.2","text":"And he wrought evil in the sight of the LORD; but not like his father, and like his mother: for he put away the image of Baal that his father had made."},{"id":"recHs6PcRU4bU1Qhy","ref":"2Kgs.3.3","text":"Nevertheless he cleaved unto the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which made Israel to sin; he departed not therefrom."},{"id":"recWrz3p8Be8mK1co","ref":"2Kgs.3.4","text":"And Mesha king of Moab was a sheepmaster, and rendered unto the king of Israel an hundred thousand lambs, and an hundred thousand rams, with the wool."},{"id":"recgr4lzwfAUEzXVr","ref":"2Kgs.3.5","text":"But it came to pass, when Ahab was dead, that the king of Moab rebelled against the king of Israel."},{"id":"recY8zFIRnr5BfFu4","ref":"2Kgs.3.6","text":"And king Jehoram went out of Samaria the same time, and numbered all Israel.","year":-895},{"id":"recx7ZGGzZKW6GI57","ref":"2Kgs.3.7","text":"And he went and sent to Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, saying, The king of Moab hath rebelled against me: wilt thou go with me against Moab to battle? And he said, I will go up: I am as thou art, my people as thy people, and my horses as thy horses.","year":-895},{"id":"recSFtGuoGF7gSgbj","ref":"2Kgs.3.8","text":"And he said, Which way shall we go up? And he answered, The way through the wilderness of Edom.","year":-895}]}
